The paper deals with neural style transfer, which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The focus of the paper is on stereoscopic images, which involves processing two views of an image to ensure consistency, making it relevant to graphics (cs.GR). The paper proposes a novel feature aggregation strategy, which involves combining information from both views, making it relevant to multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also proposes a multi-layer view loss to enforce coordination between the two paths, which involves optimizing the network, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
